Right of Use (ROU) as Stewardship Licence

Within u-Kama, a Right of Use (ROU) does not constitute ownership of land, ecological processes, or ecological memory.

ROU is defined as a stewardship licence: a conditional permission to operate within an ecological cell while maintaining the conditions required for Protection and Regeneration.

The licence grants operational authority but does not confer property rights over land, ecological value, or system outputs.

Land, ecological processes, and recorded ecological memory remain outside private ownership and are protected by doctrine and verification architecture.

⸻

Structural Principle

ROU separates custodianship, operation, and verification so that ecological continuity cannot be captured by any single actor.

